# Irek, Chishminsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan

}}
Irek (; , Ä°rek) is a rural locality (a village) in Arslanovsky Selsoviet, Chishminsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 125 as of 2010. There is 1 street.
Geography
Irek is located 5 km north of Chishmy, the district's administrative seat. Chishmy is the nearest rural locality.
